{"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile"},"abstract":[{"text":"Manages PID files for tracking running virtual machines.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Type-Properties","generated":true,"title":"Type Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/fileName"]},{"anchor":"Type-Methods","generated":true,"title":"Type Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isRunning(bundleURL:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/read(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/remove(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/terminate(bundleURL:gracePeriod:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/write(to:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/writeAndEnsureCapacity(bundleURL:vmDirectory:)"]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/pidfile"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"title":"PIDFile","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit7PIDFileO","roleHeading":"Enumeration","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}],"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}],"symbolKind":"enum"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Each running VM writes a PID file at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/<name>.vm\/pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The file contains the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"process ID of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" process that owns the VM.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Other commands (","type":"text"},{"code":"stop","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"list","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"ip","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") read the PID file to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"determine whether a VM is running and to signal the process.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"PID-File-Lifecycle","type":"heading","text":"PID File Lifecycle","level":2},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" writes the PID file before booting the VM."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"spook stop","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reads the PID file and sends SIGTERM."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" installs a SIGTERM handler that gracefully"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stops the VM, removes the PID file, and exits."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the process crashes, the PID file becomes stale."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" detects stale PID files by checking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whether the recorded process is still running."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Thread-Safety","type":"heading","text":"Thread Safety","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All methods are static and operate on the file system. They","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are safe to call from any thread. The PID file is a plain","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"text file containing a single integer, so reads and writes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are effectively atomic at the file-system level.","type":"text"}]}]}],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/PIDFile/write(to:)":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes the current process’s PID to the VM bundle directory."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/write(to:)","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/pidfile\/write(to:)","title":"write(to:)","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"write"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"to"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"URL","preciseIdentifier":"s:10Foundation3URLV"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/PIDFile/terminate(bundleURL:gracePeriod:)":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sends "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SIGTERM"},{"type":"text","text":" to the process owning the VM, waits for it to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"exit, escalates to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SIGKILL"},{"type":"text","text":" if needed, and removes the PID file."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/terminate(bundleURL:gracePeriod:)","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/pidfile\/terminate(bundleurl:gra